FBIS3-54583 "drnes019_n_94005" FBIS-NES-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Jan 1994 LEBANON Roundup of 27-28 Jan Military Actions in South Further on Wounding of Swedes NC2701204594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 2015 GMT 27 Jan 94 NC2701204594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Timor Goksel, official spokesman of the UN Interim Force in Lebanon, has announced that a preliminary investigation into the detonation of a land mine in the al-Kihyam area shows that while members of the Swedish contingent were carrying out maneuvers in a mine field, one of the soldiers made an error that triggered a mine explosion and injured three soldiers. Goksel said that one of the wounded soldiers suffered grave injuries and was transferred to Haifa's Ramban Hospital. The other two were only slightly wounded, he said.
